value.value: The directed movement of dense core granules along cytoskeletal fibers, such as microtubules or actin filaments.
Any (proper) part of the cytosol of a single cell of sufficient size to still be considered cytosol.
The region of the cytosol consisting of all cytosol that is part of the presynapse.
The region of the cytosol consisting of all cytosol that is part of the postsynapse.

Combining with a neurotransmitter and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein; promotes the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha subunit of a heterotrimeric G-protein complex.

label.value: neurotransmitter receptor activity involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential

value.value: Neurotransmitter receptor activity occurring in the postsynaptic membrane that is involved in regulating postsynaptic membrane potential, either directly (ionotropic receptors) or indirectly (e.g. via GPCR activation of an ion channel).

label.value: G protein-coupled receptor activity involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential

value.value: A G protein-coupled receptor activity occurring in the postsynaptic membrane that is part of a GPCR signaling pathway that positively regulates ion channel activity in the postsynaptic membrane.

label.value: presynaptic process involved in chemical synaptic transmission

value.value: The pathway leading to secretion of a neurotransmitter from the presynapse as part of synaptic transmission.
Cell-cell signaling to, from or within a synapse.
Cell-cell signaling in either direction across the synaptic cleft.
Cell-cell signaling to or from a synapse, mediated by a peptide.
Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse mediated by a peptide ligand crossing the synaptic cleft.
Cell-cell signaling from post to pre-synapse, across the synaptic cleft, mediated by a lipid.

label.value: protein catabolic process, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any protein degradation process, occurring at a presynapse, that regulates synaptic transmission.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: regulation of translation at synapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating translation occurring at the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, across the synaptic cleft, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: trans-synaptic signaling by neuropeptide, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, via the vesicular release and reception of neuropeptide molecules, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: trans-synaptic signaling by lipid, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, via the release and reception of lipid molecules, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: The part of synaptic transmission occurring in the post-synapse: a signal transduction pathway consisting of neurotransmitter receptor activation and its effects on postsynaptic membrane potential and the ionic composition of the postsynaptic cytosol.
Any (proper) part of the cytoplasm of a single cell of sufficient size to still be considered cytoplasm.
The portion of the cytoskeleton contained within the presynapse.
The portion of the cytoskeleton contained within the postsynapse.

label.value: regulation of protein catabolic process at synapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating protein degradation at the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: regulation of protein catabolic process at presynapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating a catabolic process occurring at a presynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: regulation of protein catabolic process at postsynapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating a catabolic process occurring at a postsynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: regulation of translation at presynapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating translation occurring at the presynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: regulation of translation at postsynapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating translation occurring at the postsynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: G protein-coupled neurotransmitter receptor activity involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential

value.value: A G protein-coupled neurotransmitter receptor activity, occurring in the postsynaptic membrane, involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential.

label.value: release of sequestered calcium ion into presynaptic cytosol

value.value: The process in which calcium ions sequestered in the endoplasmic reticulum, Golgi apparatus or mitochondria are released into the presynaptic cytosol.

label.value: release of sequestered calcium ion into postsynaptic cytosol

value.value: The process in which calcium ions sequestered in the endoplasmic reticulum, Golgi apparatus or mitochondria are released into the postsynaptic cytosol.

label.value: inorganic ion import across plasma membrane

value.value: The directed movement of inorganic ions from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of neurotransmitter receptor activity. Modulation may be via an effect on ligand affinity, or effector function such as ion selectivity or pore opening/closing in ionotropic receptors.
A process in which a protein is transported to or maintained in a location within an axon.
A process in which protein is transported from one region of the plasma membrane to another.
The directed movement of neurotransmitter receptors.
The directed movement of proteins along microtubules in neuron projections.
The directed movement of proteins along microtubules from the cell body toward the cell periphery in nerve cell axons.
The directed movement of proteins along microtubules from the cell periphery toward the cell body in nerve cell axons.
Any signal release from a synapse.
The complete extent of cell cortex that underlies some some region of the plasma membrane.

label.value: regulation of skeletal muscle contraction by action potential

value.value: Any action potential process that regulates skeletal muscle contraction.
The multiplication or reproduction of blood vessel endothelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population.
A mitotic cell cycle process which results in the assembly, arrangement, or disassembly of the nuclear inner or outer membrane during mitosis.

definition.value: This process only occurs in organisms which undergo 'closed mitosis' without nuclear breakdown.

value.value: The process in which a nuclear membrane is synthesized, aggregates, and bonds together.
Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an environmental stimulus.

label.value: regulation of inflammatory response to wounding

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response to wounding.

label.value: negative regulation of inflammatory response to wounding

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response to wounding.

label.value: positive regulation of inflammatory response to wounding

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response to wounding.

A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a prolongation or process extending from a neuron, e.g. an axon, or a dendrite.

label.value: regulation of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of vesicle fusion with Golgi apparatus.
